Emacs commands cheat sheet

MOVEMENT

C-f : forward a char
C-b : backward a char
M-f : forward a word
M-b : backwards a word
C-a : beginning of line
C-e : end of line
C-v : page down
M-v : page up
esc-< : beginning of doc
esc-> : end of doc
M-g M-g : jump to line #

BUFFERS

C-x <left-arrow> / <right-arrow> : switch buffers
C-x k <buffername> : kill a buffer; just entering return kills the current buffer
C-x b <buffername> : create a new buffer

WINDOWS

C-x 1 : Delete all windows in the selected frame except the selected window (delete-other-windows).

CODING

M-; : adds an inline comment; if a section is selected, then block comment/uncomment
C-M-\ : indents all the lines in a block

TERMINAL MODE

M-x term
in terminal mode:
C-c C-j : switch to line mode, to use emacs keybindings (edit text, switch buffers, etc.)
C-c C-k : switch to char mode, where the terminal is active (up arrow, tab complete)

SEARCH, FIND AND REPLACE

C-s : incremental forward search
M-% : query-replace 

APPEARANCE

M-x linum-mode : add line numbers to margin
